citeinfo.title: Ozone (1-Hr, O3) NAAQS Designations, Region 9, 2013, US EPA Region 9

descript.abstract: Esri polygon shapefile of 1-hour ozone designated areas in US EPA Region 9. Nonattainment areas are geographic areas which have not met National Ambient Air Quality Standards (NAAQS) for 1-hour ozone air pollution. These standards are part of the Clean Air Act. See Code of Federal Regulations, Section 40 Part 81, for detailed information about Ambient Air Quality Standards. More detailed information about NAAQS can be found on the following web page: http://www.epa.gov/air/criteria.html.
descript.purpose: This data set is specifically designed for use with ArcGIS and related software. Data may be used for reference to boundaries of attainment areas in Region 9.
descript.supplinf: Updated to include Morongo Band of Mission Indians, per 78 CFR 58189, effective October 23, 2013.

attracc.attraccr: Designations and severity classifications are based on information from the CFR

dataqual.logic: The spatial data is based on the Code of Federal Regulations - Protection of Environment, PARTS 81 TO 99, Revised as of July, 1981.
dataqual.complete: The line work is completed, all necessary lines exist for future up-dates to the polygon layer.

horizpa.horizpar: Horizontal Accuracy is based on the Public Land Survey System (BLM). The spatial data is based on Public Land Survey System (PLSS), and political boundaries such as urban, county and State boundaries, thus the line work reflects the source; for example, PLSS or county.

procstep.procdesc: step 1) Obtained official description of 1 hour ozone non-attainment geographical areas as described by Code of Federal Regulations (CFR). Step 2) Obtained arcs from Township-range, Air_districts, and political boundaries in order to create polygons in accordance with the CFR. Step 3) Added attributes to the polygons in accordance with the CFR Step 4) Created a Geodata base for the Air Designations and loaded the data
Morongo Band of Mission Indians area added using Union tool, from 2012 US Census tribal boundaries TIGER GIS data

Area designated as an ozone nonattainment area as of the date of enactment of the Clean Air Act Amendments of 1990 has not violated the national primary ambient air quality standard for ozone for the 36-month period commencing on January 1, 1987, and ending on December 31, 1989. Twelve areas were classified transitional in 1991. (See section 185A of the Clean Air Act.)

overview.eaover: Esri polygon feature class showing attainment designation areas for the pollutant 1-hour ozone. Areas designated "Nonattainment" are geographic areas which have not met National Ambient Air Quality Standards (NAAQS) for 1-hour ozone air pollution. These standards are part of the Clean Air Act. See Code of Federal Regulations, Section 40 Part 81, for detailed information about Ambient Air Quality Standards. More detailed information about NAAQS can be found on the following web page: http://www.epa.gov/air/criteria.html.
